items.name: Cerys an Craite | The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt
items.description:
Character Lora of Cerys an Craite from The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt

"Need a good slappin’ ?" -Cerys

How does salt taste like, eh Birna ? -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

My Witcher LoRA Index - soul3142's Guide to the Witcher Universe.

Main Trigger Word - cerysW3 , check examples for other ones.

Recommendations :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.7 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Steps: 25-30

  5. CFG: 7-8

  6. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: Cleave Gag
items.description:
Made an attempt at cleave gags, they're alright. Separated into two Loras, one for normal and another for knotted. The latter had a much smaller dataset and generally performs worse especially when it comes to texturing the knot, but there's at least a noticeable difference between the two. I tagged them at the same time then trained separately, so they share a trigger word.

Trigger Word:

clv

I removed all "gag"-related tags since I figured they'd interfere, but I have found that adding

cleave gag

actually improves accuracy in some cases, at least when using a bondage model. Give that a try as well if you find it's not being consistent!

I also had some instances where it was noticeably difficult to add bindings with some combinations of other Loras and I'm unsure why. Perhaps this is better suited to inpainting? I also found the knotted cleave model to be more overfit than the normal one, so I had to use a smaller CFG to compensate. It also sometimes added animal ears, no clue why.

Recommended weight: ~1.0

items.name: Mangled Merge LyCo + VAE
items.description:
Now YOU can have the power of Mangled Merge for just about 270MB with ability to set weights!

Mangled Merge LyCo works well with most v2.1 models. However, ... It goes a little off the rails with some anime based models. It makes them more ... Anime-ish and breaks with a weight of more than .5.

I've also added a vae that brings out more color and makes the image slightly darker and more contrasted. It is recommended you use the accompanying vae with Mangled Merge Lyco for best results.

The Vae file can be found here, or in this model card. It is labeled as LyCORIS (319.19 MB). Civitai didn't give me the option of labeling it as a vae, but it should save as a pickle tensor (.pt) file and you should download it into your vae folder and then select it in your settings.

After the success story of MP5, Heckler & Koch continued to develop selective firing close quarter combat SMGs, one of the development outcome and the official successor to MP5 is the UMP (Universale Maschinenpistole) series. UMP SMGs are selective fire, recoil operated and fires from a closed bolt, featuring three main variants which are designed to fire 9x19mm Parabellum, .45 ACP and .40 S&W. Compared to the older MP5 model, UMP was advertised to be more reliable, more modern and lower cost, other common features of the UMP SMGs are Picatinny rails placements (Along the top of the gun, both sides and bottom of the barrel) and a foldable buttstock.

UMP40 is the variant that chamber the .40 S&W cartridge, like the other two variants, UMP40 also features a 2-round burst fire mode, together with semi-automatic and fully automatic. Feeds on a 30-round detachable straight magazine, the weapon is able to reach a fire rate of 650 rounds per minute, reaching a muzzle velocity of 320m/s, covering up to 100 metres of effective range. Noted that UMP have their rate of fire reduced in order to compensate for the recoil generated from firing large pistol cartridge, making UMP series one of the slowest firing SMGs on the market.

items.name: Storm (X-Men) LoRA
items.description:
A character LoRA for the comic depiction and 2011 anime depiction of Storm/Ororo Munroe. Does not include her movie appearances.

Info

  • Best used at strengths 0.6. - 1. Activation tag is "Ororo" (as to not conflict with an actual storm tag). Long hair and short hair is customizable.

  • Following tags include "cape, gloves, thigh highs) mixed with "strapless, exposed shoulders" for her classic look, "midriff" for her alternate classic look, and "bodysuit, earrings" for her 2011 anime look.

  • Background will heavily skew towards sky and storm clouds if nothing else is specified.

Issues

  • Mohawk hairstyle not working at the moment, it's giving me weird braided ponytail generations right now.

  • 2011 Anime look is inconsistent but works better with more anime focused checkpoints.

  • Even though her dark skin is pruned for the activation tag, certain checkpoints will still generate white skin and white features. This is especially true for using tags like "Perfect Face/Eyes/etc." or using an inpainting of the face. This is all fixed if you specify "dark skin" in the prompt even though it's supposed to be part of the activation tag. This is not a fault with the LoRA, this is an issue with systemically biased datasets the AI is pulling from. I am having the same issue with other non-white/dark skinned characters. It's disgusting.

This Lora was made purely for a fun and self-learning experiences. I DID NOT INTEND and DO NOT give permissions for this LoRA to be used for any commercial/promotional/financial gain uses.

items.name: The Great Cthulhu - Character LoRA

"They worshiped, so they said, the Great Old Ones who lived ages before there were any men, and who came to the young world out of the sky. Those Old Ones were gone now, inside the earth and under the sea; but their dead bodies had told their secrets in dreams to the first man, who formed a cult which had never died. This was that cult, and the prisoners said it had always existed and always would exist, hidden in distant wastes and dark places all over the world until the time when the great priest Cthulhu, from his dark house in the mighty city of R'lyeh under the waters, should rise and bring the earth again beneath his sway."

Hello folks,

This LoRA was borne out of training my Delta Green style LoRAs and TI. While SD has a faint idea of what Cthulhu looks like, I thought that I could help it out. Now, you don't have to choose the lesser evil, and can summon the Great Cthulhu in all his terrible glory.

Usage Notes:

  • The model is trained on multiple interpretations of Cthulhu, so while some features are a through-line expect a fair degree of variability regardless of weight.

  • Trained on Clip Skip 1.

items.name: Ms Red.
items.description:
This is my first ever consistent-character textual inversion, I followed the handy guide produced by BelieveDiffusion, creator of the LastName series. you can find the guide HERE

For similar consistent-character embeddings by other authors check out znobody, nobody and noexist too.

For most of the example images I've used Deliberate v2. I ran this against 9 different checkpoints and the results ain't too shabby, try it! testing results below.

Instructions: Place the .pt file under stable diffusion/embeddings and then use the prompt msred_deliberatev2 - the embedding is named as such because that is the checkpoint I trained it on, but it works for other checkpoints as shown above.

Note: I could have just included all perfect images in the examples, but that's not representative. I've included some not-so-good-outputs for completeness, some are blurry/lacking fidelity because I'm still working on my upscaling process (please post tips if you have any! much appreciated)

Oh, and beware the spiderhands and ten-toes. 😉

These were all trained and generated on a 12gb RTX 3060, results were speedy and flawless for a fairly budget GPU 👍

Checkpoints tested against:

  • SD 1.5

  • Realistic Vision v2.0

  • HARDblend-NSFW

  • GalaxyTimeMachine's GTM "ForYou-Fantasy" v1.1

  • Deliberate v2

  • Clarity 2

  • Avalon TruVision v3.1

  • AnalogMadness v4.0

Credit to the authors of the above for some smashing models.

If I do any more of these I will tag them under dtmiss

Disclaimer: this is a fictional character and a experiment, any resemblance to actual persons is entirely coincidental.
